when is the best time to water flowers and the grass in the morning for my zone if you get water on roses and it doesn't have the day to evaporate you get mildew also watering in the evening is a way to encourage snails to come out and slither all over the plants even more than they already do however if it has been a hot day water them both morning and evening afternoon watering is just a waste of water too much evaporation unless your plants are looking at you and saying that they will die of thirst in the next minutes without water bottom line use your best judgment on what works best for your zone Evaporation Desert Brewery Daylight saving time Xeriscaping Rose Perfume Air conditioning Dorama Lake Weather lore Hyperthermia Fossil fuel power plant Fog Water Death Valley National Park Dehydration USS Flier (SS-250) Honey Ecohydrology Tea Atlantic Ocean Coffee Renewable energy USS S-32 (SS-137) Wildfire Sodium carbonate Leaf 2003 North America blackout Craters of the Moon National Monument and Preserve Irrigation Steam engine Town gas Hiking Canonical hours Flower USS Ammen (DD-527) Deforestation Compost Houseplant Water resources 1980 eruption of Mount St. Helens USS Uhlmann (DD-687) Perennial plant Sugar beet Thermoregulation Boiling point USS Tunny (SS-282) Dry cleaning WNNX (FM) Desertification Carnivorous plant Fox Kids Customs and etiquette of Japan USS Seadragon (SS-194) USS Waters (DD-115) WZZN Jewish services Autonomous building Ocean thermal energy conversion Wheat Goblin Valley State Park Mountain Gorilla Operation Market Garden USS Yorktown (CV-10) IND Chrystie Street Connection Hydrotherapy Meal Morning glory Geography of Seychelles Elis Prefecture Instant coffee Yom Kippur Shaggy dog story USS Whale (SS-239) USS Tang (SS-306) AFI 100 Years series Sorghum Sweating Garden Strawberry Hemp USS Taylor (DD-468) Deep lake water cooling Ecology Aarti Velvet Revolver International Date Line STS-59 Solar power Espresso Twelve leverage points Holy Week Apocalyps